In hearing charges directly preferred (crimina), the jury looks to the defendant’s advocate for a complete and comprehensive refutation, without any idea of ‘ making a present to the accused of more in the direction of, or in order to secure, acquittal' (ad salutem), i.e. of crediting him with a greater degree of innocence than his counsel can show warrant for.
